title: International Night
description: After 3 years of absence, International Night is back. Please save the date! May 19th at 5PM. Organization of International Students (OIS) are working hard to plan the event and would love for you to join us as volunteers or performers. Please scan the QR codes on the flyer to sign up. We will meet up with our volunteers next term. This is a great way for you to get involve with OIS and other international students and practice planning the event with us! If you have any questions, feel free to contact ois@pdx.edu.

title: Iftar Tuesdays
description: The Rose City Book Pub will offer Iftar every Tuesday during Ramadan starting at sunset. Then it is the special for the next few days until it runs out. Offerings include choice of lamb or chicken kabsah, hummus, tabbouleh, tsatsiki, pita, and date.

title: Outta this World Disco
description: All the way from outer space - Come ready to groove at Outta This World Disco! Stop by Parkway North for games, face painting, and disco dancing! Intergalactic groovy space attired encouraged!

title: Pitch Slapped!
description: Get ready to get Pitch Slapped! With a live showing of Pitch Perfect and free movie theater snacks! We will also be having a special performance and live riff-off by @thegreennote. Come join us with a blanket and some comfy clothes to get your pitch on!

title: Test Your Mood
description: Test Your Mood on Wednesday, March 15th from 3:30-5pm with ISSS at the Karl Miller Center (KMC) 650 Lounge. Counseling is offering FREE mental health check-ups for PSU students. Tea and cookies will be provided. Students will also have the opportunity to enter into a raffle to win prizes. Hope to see you there!

title: Inclusion & Access  Craft & Cozy
description: Join the Inclusion & Access Committee for a relaxed craft night with snacks and tea! It will be on Thursday, February 23 from 4:00 - 6:00 PM. We'll have various crafts to keep your creativity flowing, so come on down and chill with us.

title: Bowling & Indian Bites
description: Join Basic Needs Hub, Food Pantry, International Student Office, Resource Center for Students with Children, and ASPSU Global Community! This Thursday from 2:00 - 4:00 we will share Indian food to comfort Indian students, the most significant international student population, with domestic students who might enjoy different cultural cuisine. Get to know everyone by creating a space to share food and play games together, and hopefully come together as a big Portland State Family!

title: Virtual Game Night
description: Game with us this Thursday from 4:00-6:00 PM through Zoom! Inclusion & Access is hosting a game night, so if you're a homebody who wants to make friends, get involved! We'll have a ton of different games and opportunities to connect with different peers and members of the Inclusion & Access Committee! Click Below to save the Zoom Link or more info.
